LETSHEGO Bank Tanzania will tomorrow hold business stakeholders engagement on Twitter through Connect Spaces to promote inclusive finance transformation to digital for the benefit of customers, suppliers and communities across Africa. The Bank’s Chief Executive Officer, Omar Msangi said in Dar es Salaam over the weekend that the engagement was an important initiative showing how the bank value digital technology in providing high quality services to its customers. “In Tanzania, our customers can look forward to new solutions in insurance and payments, all available with a few clicks via our digital mall channels and this twitter discussion is valuable and of more importance to our bank,” he said. He added that it is the celebration of collaborative regional efforts of Letshego while promoting inclusive finance transformation to digital for the benefit of customers, suppliers and communities across Africa. Twitter Space is a unique and fast-growing space for widely-known community trailblazers to share personal insights into their own experiences, learning and unpack the ingredients for success that brought them the opportunities they celebrate and build on today. In 2021, Letshego progressed its digital strategy by launching the ‘LetsGo Digital Mall’ in ten markets across sub-Saharan Africa. The LetsGo Digital Mall is an Omnichannel integrated platform that customers can access via Web, WhatsApp USSD and Mobile.